reviews.text: Great food!! We went twice during our vacation. Shrimp Crab Seafood soup was delicious and super creamy, really filled you up. All food was simply spot-on. Service was also very welcoming. Would definitely recommend!

Side Door Cafe was extremely satisfying. We came here for the first time on Valentine’s Day. We came here at night it was very cute from the outside, as well walking in to the restaurant. We made reservations and was seated right away to our table. The waitress took her time with us and made sure we knew all the specials. I ordered the crusted herb salmon with rice and asparagus and it was cooked to perfection. My husband got the seafood fettuccine and he was very happy with the amount of seafood that was in the pasta. They went a little above and beyond putting red rose petals on our table to set the romantic feel for the night. We wish we had room for dessert but we were to full to try, gives us a good reason to come back. Thank you for a wonderful night with delicious food. Highly recommend for couples who are looking for a romantic dinner night out.

We love this place! Great atmosphere, the most friendly and helpful service, and delicious food. What more can you ask for? We liked it so much, we came back two nights in a row. My new favorite spot for dinner. Thank you!

Being two young kids without a reservation and a little under dressed we walked in kinda feeling a little out of place. Nobody seemed to care though, everybody was extremely polite. The food was very flavorful and the portions were very large. The desserts were so good coconut cream pie was the best my boyfriend has ever had. 
The price was very reasonable. 
We even left with leftovers. 
Would defiently go here again.

This restaurant has no lack of satisfied patrons, both locals and visitors, so you'll want to make a reservation, especially on the weekend.  It's located off the main highway (101) on the ocean side going towards Glenagen, and it's a welcomed relief in an area that caters to tourist families looking for fast food, chowder, deep fried fish and burgers.  
The quality of the cocktails, freshly made entrees and service are absolutely first class, we've never been disappointed and always look forward to our next visit.

The food is amazing, the service was friendly. Everything on the menu looked wonderful - we wanted to try it all! The staff was attentive but not invasive. It was a fantastic experience. We WILL be back during our visit and for all future visits! I highly recommend this place.
Great atmosphere. Quiet and nice. Still laid back and friendly. The copianni was amazing. All the flavors were separated perfectly. If you are looking for a memorable dish this place is a must!
Incredible food! The menu and quality are better than most high-end restaurants in the city. And the service was friendly, informed, and thoughtful. Thank you for the wonderful meal and experience!

We stopped here for the first time over New Year's Eve 2019. It is a little on the spending side, but worth every penny! The food is phenomenal and the customer service is exceptional. We dressed casually and were treated with respect. I highly recommend Blackfish Cafe!

I come here every trip to Lincoln City for the salmon because NO place cooks salmon better!!   The salmon caesar salad is very good and gluten free!   They get it right every time for years now!   The steamer clams are to die for also with the broth it comes in hands down the very best I've ever had!  Other places it's always overly salty but perfectly done here at Blackfish!   They are very accommodating for food allergies and most of the menu is gluten free.   It's always a pleasure to be greeted by Linda the lovely hostess as well!  Thank you again!

We ordered take out for our anniversary dinner. But as is always as is with the restaurants I go to, my order got screwed up. I ordered a salmon dish that came with mashed potatoes and asparagus, I believe, but instead got the blackened salmon that comes with pasta. I was very disappointed as I was eagerly awaiting the other dish. But fortunately the dish was very good! The pasta had an amazing flavor! Although I didn't feel like eating pasta that day, I gobbled it all up. The salmon was very tender and flaky but lacked something in flavor, could be because that's not what I wanted to eat in the first place though. My husband ordered the fish & chips, which he loved. We also ordered the espresso pie for dessert which was amazing! It was the highlight of our meal. I gave it 5 stars even though I didn't get exactly what I ordered, because the food was delicious, service was excellent and the ambient of the restaurant was relaxing!

The location is amazing with gorgeous seaside views, lovely decor and atmosphere, and great service. They have a fantastic happy hour menu— the calamari and grass fed cheeseburger were absolutely fantastic. The wedge salad and clam chowder were also great. Will definitely be back!

This place was very good.  Took the whole family...the kids meal could use some help but whatever.  My wife got a steak that was very good.  

Enough about that...the waiter recommended Hal Mac which is basically Halibut with crab, cheese, some magic sauce, and crack on top.  It was the best seafood dish I have had in a very long time...(many years).  It was top ten best meals I have ever had in my life...  Do not miss this.  

The baguette while waiting was warm and delicious.  The service was impeccable, with several waiters servicing our table at different times when dishes were empty...they were always smiling.  I’ll be back...perhaps in my dreams many time before I am back in person...but I will be back.  Hal Mac is one of those dishes you travel great distances for...you enjoy every bite of...and you lick the plate when it’s gone (no matter who’s looking).  My only wish was that there was a mini Hal Mac on the desert menu... The marionberry cobbler with vanilla ice cream was awesome as well though.
The location and view are nice, and staff was good but wished they took the food up a notch to match the prices. I have had better fish tacos elsewhere. The Marion Berry cobbler was only ok.
Delicious! Right on the Beach to enjoy your meal with a lovely view. Excellent service! Highly recommend

Delicious sandwiches, tots were cooked perfectly, fair prices, and staff was friendly. Great music, b&w cartoons, and memorabilia abounds. I dig their gear as well, very reasonable from beginning to end. No pictures, just go grab a hot meal and take your own. :)

Very good food! Although overall service wasn’t too good. The servers were very sweet. But I noticed people started coming in after us, and getting their food before us. It took 45 minutes for us to get our food when for other people it took 10-15 minutes. When my dad got his food (finally), it was the wrong sandwich. My hamburger was right the first time and we both enjoyed our meals but I just don’t get why it took 45 mins. for us. Like I said, excellent food, the servers were very sweet and caring, and I really liked the style of the place.

New owner and newly renovated. Now has an outdoor patio. Food and service have improved significantly. Honestly my husband and I shared the best Reuben sandwich and chili dog we’ve EVER had just the other day! They make their own kraut and slow cook their own corned beef, which is prepared as tender “chunks” on the sandwich. Delicious! Ice cream shakes are still the best you will find on the coast. If you haven’t been lately... I cannot recommend them more highly!

Excellent food and excellent service!!! My server was Kevin. He made my meal, my milkshake, my experience the best I have ever had at any restaurant. With the 60s music that they have playing and all the 60s memorabilia makes me wish I was there too see it back in the day but 60s cafe is the closest experience I have to it and I must say a wonderful one. Thank you for making my experience great with your happy hour, sliders, and amazing spicy chicken wings. I will be back anytime I visit the coast. I highly recommend!

Was looking for a nice chowder house but everything closed around 4 on a Monday in town. So I ended up going here and still ordering some chowder. Thought it might not as good because this place is known for there burgers. Non the less i ordered the clam chowder and it did not disappoint. Very taste and had some garlic bread with it,excellent choice. Service was great and a very nice waiter we had. I did not get his name but he was fast and friendly. Next time I will try the milkshakes!

Great food!! We went twice during our vacation. Shrimp Crab Seafood soup was delicious and super creamy, really filled you up. All food was simply spot-on. Service was also very welcoming. Would definitely recommend!

If you can get over the occasional pubic hair in your food and appreciate a shop with vegan food and clown stripper servers, you'll do fine. All you can eat, though? Not the case.

I would be very concerned about finding gregs semen in my soup again. It was not funny the first time , but they Love it So much Joy for everyone. The corrupt family from LC owners. scummy whitetrash. They give drugs to kids.

I agree with all the 1 star reviews. I believe the only reason this place stays in business is because it's the only large pizza place in Lincoln City!  The only worse pizza I know is at Chuck-E-Cheese.  
Owners, you have a prime spot in LC don't waste it making bad pizza, improve and add more sauce and better grade of cheese? You really need to improve before another pizza place opens up, otherwise you will be going out of business.  Gordon Ramsay should roll through here maybe you'll listen to him?
   Update: I am giving you an extra star for at least responding kindly to my review, even though with a deaf ear.  I suspect that most of your 5 star reviews are from employees, friends and family.  Just to give you a little more info; I have 7 kids, who will eat just about any kind of food yet voiced their displeasure about your pizza, I assure you, there is something not quite right about your pizza if it gets that response from my kids and their friends.  The crust was good and toppings ok, but the sauce is bland and barely any on the pizza, plus the cheese was dumped on top and looked very unpleasing.  You can do better!!
First time eating her, really good pizza! And a surprisingly large video game selection, including a couple of pinball tables. Had a good visit, well definitely eat here again next time I'm in town.

We've been to Gallucci's a few times over the last couple of years. Hoping that it will have improved each time. Sadly, WE continue to be disssapointed with the pizza, especially the crust. If you're going to serve a very, very dry pizza crust it should be a thin crust. The crust is dry & flavorless, furthermore, there is very little pizza/tomato sauce which adds to the dryness. I think you get the picture. They do have a good salad bar that is fresh with good ingredients. If you want salad go to Gallucci's. If you want pizza don't...

The pizza is amazing. The kids always have a  Blast. A great place to have a kids birthday party. It always gets busy on the weekends because it's so good. And there is overflow to the arcade next  Door. You can eat pizza at the arcade You can eat your food and have fun at the same time

Pizza is ok ,  we showed up 15 min late with our group and the pizza was cold. It would have been nice to put it in boxes as they came out  in stead of just sitting on the counter. Too much cheese in my opinion. Very expensive. Nice seating and atmosphere too. It would also be nice to have a soda machine in stead of relying on pitchers of expensive soda.

Amazing service and food. Took the whole family and everyone was extremely happy. The service was so fantastic and we enjoyed our food so much we ate breakfast and went back for dinner too. I would highly suggest trying them.
Food was wonderful,  breakfast available until later so that was nice.  Great service.  Everything we had appeared to be made from scratch and not prepared/ frozen foods.  Delicious!!!

Wow! Fantastic food and serving sizes! We loved our waiter Cameron, he was attentive and kind😊 a little pricey but worth every penny. We will always stop here for now on! (PS- You have to try the key lime pie here AMAZING)

When our family first moved to Oregon, The Dory Cove was where we celebrated our 7 wedding anniversary, and we visited again today for #14! 
Great service, very attentive and food was excellent just like our previous experiences! Definitely a must while on the coast for great dinning!!

The restaurant was highly rated by a close friend of mine.  The menu is wonderful, the service is great, the prices seem reasonable.  I ordered Crab Stuffed Halibut... and the crab was shredded...and very light--so light I  couldn't taste it.  I'll try the crab and cheese next time...
